      "description": "Group Policy Preferences XML under SYSVOL Policies. Groups.xml / Drives.xml / Services.xml / ScheduledTasks.xml / DataSources.xml / Printers.xml historically embedded AES-256 'cpassword' (MS14-025) reversible to cleartext. Even on patched DCs, legacy XML often remains. Black AD-engagement primitive. Closes Snaffler #31."
    },
    {
      "rule_name": "ShareSiftKeepGermanCredFilenames",
      "triage": "Red",
      "match_action": "Snaffle",
      "match_location": "FileName",
      "wordlist_type": "Regex",
      "wordlist": [
        "(Kennw(oe|\u00f6|o)rter|Passw(oe|\u00f6|o)rter|Anmeldedaten|Logindaten|Zug(ae|\u00e4|a)ng(e|es)?|Schl(ue|\u00fc|u)ssel)"
      ],
      "description": "German credential-keyword filenames. ML path classifier returns ~0.0 on non-English vocab. Corporate-Europe coverage gap. Operator (#53) reported their German keyword rules silently shadowed by Snaffler's English defaults; the pure ShareSift engine doesn't have the ordering issue but lacked the vocab. Covers both umlaut and 'oe'/'ae'/'ue' transliterated spellings."
    },
    {
      "rule_name": "ShareSiftKeepWireguardPrivateKey",
      "triage": "Black",
      "match_action": "Snaffle",
      "match_location": "FileContentAsString",
      "wordlist_type": "Regex",
      "wordlist": [
        "(^|\\n)\\s*PrivateKey\\s*=\\s*[A-Za-z0-9+/]{42,44}={0,2}\\s*(\\n|$)"
      ],
      "description": "WireGuard config file with embedded PrivateKey. The 32-byte Curve25519 private key is base64-encoded (44 chars w/ trailing '='). The file IS the credential \u2014 possession = VPN access. Black on match. Operator (#119) flagged that VPN credentials in plaintext is a common corporate-share finding."
    },
    {
      "rule_name": "ShareSiftKeepOpenvpnAuthUserPassRef",
      "triage": "Red",
