      "description": "Cisco IOS enable secret / password / username password commands. Type 0 = cleartext, type 5 = MD5, type 7 = trivially reversible Vigenere obfuscation, type 8/9 = modern PBKDF2/scrypt. Even type-8 is offline-crackable. Red. Closes Snaffler #78 thread (Cisco config rules contributed by hkelley)."
